<br>
Many, many hards later it's pretty routine now.<br>
<br>
Lull does have its place in Hards.  However, you should focus your split work using mezz &amp; snare.  The only time I break out Lull is to separate groups of 4+ mobs by breaking the agro chain.  Otherwise, as others have eluded to, the high resist rate makes it too time consuming.<br>
<br>
With a 305 cha I find crit resists to be very rare.  Frequently less than 1x per dungeon.  Also, the mezz resist rate does seem to be quite improved by the high CHA.  The shaman I group with most often hits me with the CHA buff automatically now.<br>
<br>
Best advice I can give is get as much FT as you can via augs, AA abilities and gear.  You're going to need to fade from time to time and with a little bad luck or a whopper room you may need to do it several times. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub147.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=triliansoulwind>TrilianSoulwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 194<br> <font color=#330000>(3/17/04 11:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallontour.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=307.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lull doesn't belong in hards</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I've only done one hard, and it was apparently the hardest (Tak). I did the &quot;fools ploy&quot; using SSoQ. Keep in mind that I don't have Morrell yet, though from what I saw, perhaps 1 in 6 or 7 mobs was white, so most were mezzable.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
