 then lull and can usually get 1-2 at a time (of course I can also spot when lull isn't needed).  I like lull because I don't like to fade unless it is absolutely necc. and lull can often split 1-2 mobs out of a pack before you even start your pull.  I use the mez trick too, if I have 2, mez one off a little ways, get the other to camp and mez it, then re-mez the first one.  I tend to set it up, so I basically always have 1 mob mezed in camp (or in the doorway to the room) when the previous mob dies.  I like to use HoS on the pull so I have a better chance of landing my initial slow, but otherwise don't use HoS because mez resists are rare for me (I use the 65 mez, but don't have max cha or anything).<br>
As stated, the key to pulling hards is to have atleast 1 room or hallway between your group and the stuff yer pulling at all times (yell at your group if they move up early...that's fine in normals, but it's a no-no in hards).  Also, as stated, you simply have to keep trying hards until you have your own strategy worked out and know exactly how you want to pull.  Eventually you will figure it out.<br>
I've never had any trouble with the mobs in Sro...never been able to figure out why people think Sro is hardest...Nro or EF is the hardest of the hards to me (due to mob placement and MR).  I can however second that CHA helps with resist rate of lull, critical lull, and indeed MEZ (chanters mezing in rathe prove that cha makes a big difference in mez resists).  I've also heard that singing mod affects resist rates on lull and mez(the singing versions), but never actually tested it or seen test results. <p>Impressario Minerian Lutestrummer, lev 65 bard<br>
