<br>
Like Minerian, I wasn't ready for hards when I started, but now have over 7k hps, full defensive AAs, FT 14, etc. My advice is to stop and think for a moment before pulling every room. Each room is it's own pulling challenge. If you can mezz/split, then do so. It's far more reliable than lull. If you can't, figure out which one to lull to get the max effect. You're unlikely to be able to lull more than 2 before the timer wears off. Definitely use the cha song and consider buying planar power (cha 305 is the win) if you're going to lull. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub147.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wyndaria>wyndaria</A></span><br> Posts: 201<br> <font color=#330000>(3/29/04 5:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallontour.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=307.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> My regular hunting group had our first unassisted Hard win last night, and I can tell you.  WHAT A THRILL!!!  <br>
